  <body>
    <header>
      <para styleclass="Heading1">Dialog: Movie</para>
    </header>
    <para styleclass="Heading2" style="page-break-before:always;">Movie</para>
    <para styleclass="VariableName"><text styleclass="Body Text">When you continuously-cycle a model, commercial video-recording software may not record each step in a machine-cycle. Also, it is difficult to record exactly one machine-cycle. The </text><text styleclass="T_Menu">Movie</text><text styleclass="Body Text"> command solves these problems.</text></para>
    <para styleclass="Body Text HowTo"><table styleclass="Default" rowcount="1" colcount="1">
      <tr style="vertical-align:top">
        <td>
          <para styleclass="Body Text">Use the <text styleclass="Interface2">Movie</text><text styleclass="Interface"> dialog</text> to: </para>
          <list id="0" type="ul" listtype="bullet" formatstring="&#183;" format-charset="SYMBOL_CHARSET" levelreset="true" legalstyle="false" startfrom="1" styleclass="HowTo Bulleted" style="font-family:Symbol; font-size:11pt; color:#000000;">
            <li styleclass="HowTo Bulleted">arrange the area of the “frame” in the graphics-area to record as a movie</li>
            <li styleclass="HowTo Bulleted">browse to a path and enter a file-name for the movie</li>
            <li styleclass="HowTo Bulleted">control the start and end of the Movie as a function of the Master-Machine-Angle.</li>
          </list>
          <para styleclass="Body Text">You can <text styleclass="HowTo Bulleted">record and save:</text></para>
          <list id="0" type="ul" listtype="bullet" formatstring="&#183;" format-charset="SYMBOL_CHARSET" levelreset="true" legalstyle="false" startfrom="1" styleclass="HowTo Bulleted" style="font-family:Symbol; font-size:11pt; color:#000000;">
            <li styleclass="HowTo Bulleted">a movie as a GIF file-type</li>
          </list>
          <para styleclass="Interface2">or</para>
          <list id="1" type="ul" listtype="bullet" formatstring="&#183;" format-charset="SYMBOL_CHARSET" levelreset="true" legalstyle="false" startfrom="1" styleclass="HowTo Bulleted" style="font-family:Symbol; font-size:11pt; color:#000000;">
            <li styleclass="HowTo Bulleted">a sequence of images as <text styleclass="Interface2">PNG, JPG</text>, <text styleclass="Interface2">JPeG</text>, or <text styleclass="Interface2">BMP</text> file-type</li>
          </list>
          <para styleclass="Body Text HowTo">We append for you a number to each image. The numbers are 000, 001, 002, ... </para>
          <para styleclass="Interface2">or</para>
          <list id="2" type="ul" listtype="bullet" formatstring="&#183;" format-charset="SYMBOL_CHARSET" levelreset="true" legalstyle="false" startfrom="1" styleclass="HowTo Bulleted" style="font-family:Symbol; font-size:11pt; color:#000000;">
            <li styleclass="HowTo Bulleted">save one image as a snapshot of the model.</li>
          </list>
          <para styleclass="Normal"><line style="height:1px; color:#343400;" /></para>
          <para styleclass="Notes">Notes:</para>
          <para styleclass="Body Text HowTo">The <text styleclass="Interface2">GIF</text> format produces a large file when the size and the number of frames are large.</para>
          <para styleclass="Body Text HowTo">You can edit the size of the frame and the number-of-frames in the <text styleclass="T_Menu">Movie dialog</text>.</para>
          <para styleclass="Normal"><line style="height:1px; color:#343400;" /></para>
          <para styleclass="Body Text"><text styleclass="VariableName">Top-Tips</text></para>
          <list id="3" type="ul" listtype="bullet" formatstring="&#183;" format-charset="SYMBOL_CHARSET" levelreset="true" legalstyle="false" startfrom="1" styleclass="HowTo Bulleted" style="font-family:Symbol; font-size:11pt; color:#000000;">
            <li styleclass="HowTo Bulleted"><text styleclass="VariableName" style="color:#ff0000;">Before</text> you start the <text styleclass="T_Menu">Movie</text> command, move the <text styleclass="VariableName">Master-Machine-Angle</text> to zero(0). Click <text styleclass="T_Menu">Run menu</text><text styleclass="Body Text"> &gt; </text><text styleclass="T_Menu">Home</text><text styleclass="Body Text"> or </text><text styleclass="T_Menu">ALT+H</text><text styleclass="Body Text"> keyboard shortcut.</text></li>
            <li styleclass="HowTo Bulleted"><text styleclass="Body Text HowTo">Do not append the file-name with a number</text></li>
          </list>
        </td>
      </tr>
    </table></para>
    <para styleclass="VariableName"><anchor id="Dialog-MakeMovieFileTypes"><keywords><keyword>Make Movie dialog<keyword>File-types</keyword></keyword></keywords></anchor><text styleclass="Heading3_atocs_">Movie dialog</text></para>
    <para styleclass="Body Text"><table styleclass="Default" rowcount="1" colcount="2">
      <tr style="vertical-align:top">
        <td style="width:245px;">
          <para styleclass="Normal"><image src="MD-Dialog-MakeMovie.png" scale="-99.90%" styleclass="Image Caption" figurelistinclude="0"><caption><![CDATA[Make-Movie dialog]]></caption></image></para>
        </td>
        <td>
          <para styleclass="Separator-Header"><text styleclass="Body Text">When you start the </text><text styleclass="T_Menu">Movie</text><text styleclass="Body Text"> command, you see a rectangle in the graphics-area. </text></para>
          <para styleclass="Separator-Header"><text styleclass="Body Text">You record everything inside the rectangle. </text></para>
          <para styleclass="Separator-Header"><text styleclass="Body Text">The rectangle is the what we call the </text><text styleclass="ParameterHeader">Frame</text><text styleclass="Body Text">. </text></para>
          <para styleclass="Separator-Header"><text styleclass="Body Text">You can edit the size and position of the </text><text styleclass="ParameterHeader">Frame</text><text styleclass="Body Text">.</text></para>
        </td>
      </tr>
    </table></para>
    <para styleclass="Body Text HowTo"><anchor id="MakeMoviedialogr10-Filenames" styleclass="Separator-Header"><keywords><keyword>Make Movie dialog<keyword>Frame Size</keyword><keyword>Frame Position</keyword></keyword></keywords></anchor><image src="tog_plus.gif" scale="100.00%" styleclass="Separator-Header" figurelistinclude="0"></image><toggle type="dropdown" print-expanded="true" help-expanded="false" defaultstyle="false" src-collapsed="tog_plus.gif" src-expanded="tog_minus.gif" styleclass="Separator-Header"><caption><![CDATA[ Frame Size and Position ]]></caption></toggle></para>
    <para styleclass="Body Text HowTo"><table styleclass="Default" rowcount="1" colcount="2">
      <tr style="vertical-align:top">
        <td style="width:245px;">
          <para styleclass="Image Caption"><image src="MD-Dialog-MakeMovie-FrameSizePosition.png" scale="-99.90%" figurelistinclude="0"></image></para>
        </td>
        <td>
          <para styleclass="Body Text"><table styleclass="Block" rowcount="1" colcount="1">
            <tr style="vertical-align:top">
              <td>
                <list id="4" type="ol" listtype="decimal" formatstring="&#37;&#48;&#58;&#115;&#46;" format-charset="DEFAULT_CHARSET" levelreset="true" legalstyle="false" startfrom="1" styleclass="Bullets" style="font-family:&apos;Segoe UI Semibold&apos;; font-size:11pt; font-weight:bold; color:#000000;">
                  <li styleclass="Bullets">Use the <text styleclass="Parameter">Pre-select a Frame Size</text>... drop-down list-box to select a typical frame size.<text styleclass="VariableName">&#32;</text></li>
                </list>
                <para styleclass="VariableName">OR </para>
                <list id="5" type="ol" listtype="decimal" formatstring="&#37;&#48;&#58;&#115;&#46;" format-charset="DEFAULT_CHARSET" levelreset="true" legalstyle="false" startfrom="1" styleclass="Bullets" style="font-family:&apos;Segoe UI Semibold&apos;; font-size:11pt; font-weight:bold; color:#000000;">
                  <li styleclass="Bullets">Edit the <text styleclass="Parameter">Width</text> and <text styleclass="Parameter">Height</text> of the frame.<text styleclass="VariableName">&#32;</text></li>
                </list>
                <list id="6" type="ol" listtype="decimal" formatstring="&#37;&#48;&#58;&#115;&#46;" format-charset="DEFAULT_CHARSET" levelreset="true" legalstyle="false" startfrom="2" styleclass="Bullets" style="font-family:&apos;Segoe UI Semibold&apos;; font-size:11pt; font-weight:bold; color:#000000;">
                  <li styleclass="Bullets">Edit the <text styleclass="Parameter">Left</text> and <text styleclass="Parameter">Top</text><text styleclass="Parameter-Header" style="font-family:Arial; font-size:10pt; font-weight:normal; font-style:normal; text-decoration:none; text-transform:none; vertical-align:baseline; color:#000000; background-color:transparent; letter-spacing:normal; letter-scaling:100%;">&#32;</text>of the <text style="font-weight:normal;">frame</text><text styleclass="VariableName">. </text></li>
                </list>
              </td>
            </tr>
          </table></para>
          <para styleclass="Body Text"><text styleclass="Normal">The rectangle should now be the area in which you want to record.</text></para>
        </td>
      </tr>
    </table></para>
